title: Irssi, Bitlbee and Facebook Chat
layout: post
---
So today I managed to connect Irssi to Facebook Chat through Bitlbee. First things first, get Irssi and Bitlbee.
<!-- more start -->
$ sudo port install irssi
$ sudo port install bitlbee

If you don't knwo what this commands mean read <a href="http://osxforlinuxfreaks.wordpress.com/2012/01/09/the-macports/" target="_blank">this</a>. Then configure bitlbee.

$ cp /opt/local/etc/bitlbee/bitlbee.conf.sample /opt/local/etc/bitlbee/bitlbee.conf


$ bitlebee
$ irssi

<p>Right now you're in irssi's console mode. Run the following to get things working. These commands should be easy to understand.</p>

$ /connect localhost
$ account add jabber username@chat.facebook.com password

<p>The following renames friend list default names to readable names.</p>

$ account fb set nick_source full_name

<p>Start the chat.</p>

$ account on

<p>And it is done. Now you should learn about irssi. Quick tip to start a conversation:</p>
$ /query Name
<p>Bellow is a screenshot of mine. And to get it in a separate window run "/window new hide" before.</p>

<a href="http://osxforlinuxfreaks.files.wordpress.com/2012/03/captura-de-ecracc83-2012-03-10-acc80s-22-28-47.png"><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-226" title="Irssi, Bitlbee and Facebook Chat Screenshot" src="http://osxforlinuxfreaks.files.wordpress.com/2012/03/captura-de-ecracc83-2012-03-10-acc80s-22-28-47.png?w=300" alt="" width="300" height="110" /></a>

